                     <interp inst="t18280911-236-victim1339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who are <rs id="t18280911-236-viclabel1212" type="occupation">ironmongers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-236-victim1337 t18280911-236-viclabel1212"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-236-victim1339 t18280911-236-viclabel1212"></join>. The prisoner was in their employ on the 25th of August; I know this mat to be their property - they had received it with some things a few days before; I had not quite unsewn it, and when it was returned it was exactly in the same state - I cannot speak to the other things, but one of them has the name on; they are all such articles as they sell.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-236-person1340">
                  ROBERT 
                  BARNES
               <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1340" type="surname" value="BARNES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1340" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1340" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Messrs. Granges. On Monday, the 25th of August, I was desired to follow the prisoner, which I did to his own house; I then asked him how he came to take the mat, which was then under his arm - he said he thought it was of little or no value; it was charged to us about 2s. or 2s. 3d. - these tools were found in the prisoner's house by the constable, in my presence; I believe them to be my employers'.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-236-person1341">
                  JOHN 
                  FERNE
               <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1341" type="surname" value="FERNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1341" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1341" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I went to the prisoner's, and found these articles.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Mr. Barnes came to me, and said I had got a mat that did not belong to me; I said I would take it back - he said it did not matter about my taking it back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-236-person1342">
                  ROBERT 
                  BARNES
               <interp inst="t18280911-236-person1342" type="surname" value="BARNES"></interp>
